Panels
1. Remove all panels: Right click on panel -> Panel preferences -> (+) create new, (-) select and remove old ones
2. Right click on newly created blanck panel -> Panel preferences ->
	+ Display
		+ Mode = vertical
		+ Automatically hide the oanel = Intelligently
		+ Row size = 30
		+ Number of rows = 1
		+ Length = 100
	+ Appearance
		+ Background -> Alpha = 100
	+ Items
	  + (-) Remove -> Choose everything and remove
		+ (+) Add -> Whisker Menu(apt install xfce4-whiskermenu-plugin)
			+ Click Whisker Menu - choose edit option on the right
				+ Apperance - Show application tooltips(OFF)
				+ Apperance - Show category names(OFF)
				+ Behavior - Position search entry next to panel button(ON)
				+ Behavior - Position categories next to pnael button(ON)
				+ Behavior - Recently used - Amount of items(0)
		+ (+) Add -> Windows Buttons
			+ Click on Windows buttons, choose edit option on the right
			 + Every toggle except shows on all monitors(OFF)
		+ (+) Add -> Separator
		 + Click on spearator, choose edit option on the right -> Expand(ON), Style(TRANSPARENT)

Settings
Settings Manager
	+ Keyboard - Application Shortcuts
		+ Choose each(except xflock4) - (-) Remove
		+ Choose one of the xflock4(remove the other) - Edit - xflock4 - meta + L
		+ (+) Add - xfce4-popup-whiskermenu - Meta(one key)
	+ Appearance
		+ Style - Adwaita-dark
		+ Icons - Adwaita
	+ Desktop
		+ Background - Change wallpaper
		+ Icons - Default icons - All except Removable Devices(OFF)

# Not recommended all after xfce4-notes
Remove - sudo apt remove libreoffice libreoffice-draw libreoffice-base libreoffice-calc libreoffice-math libreoffice-writer libreoffice-common xfce4-notes xfburn xsane ristretto exfalso # parole 
sudo apt autoremove

